description.plain:
On August 4th, 2022, Katie Gregson-Macleod first posted about Complex (demo) when she published a minute long clip on TikTok with the caption: “here’s my saviour complex song.”

The clip quickly gained traction and within the first four days it racked up 2.5 million views and over 500K likes. The comment section was full of people relating to the lyrics of the song, as well as pop stars Maisie Peters, Gracie Abrams, Mae Muller and Fletcher among others posting their praise.

annotations:
Triangular, I can see them now
 Three points at which I let myself down

This may be a reference to the Karpman drama triangle, a social model of human relationships, in which there is a villain/persecutors, saviour/rescuers, and victim. It is a type of destructive relationship, and fits with the concept of a ‘saviour complex’, as individuals may become entrenched in a certain mindset, believing themselves to be the rescuers of others.
I think he’s a good guy

This ties into the theme of having a “savior complex.” Despite the subject of this song treating the narrator poorly, she refuses to see it because she wants to fix them and make them change for the better. Many people with savior complexes have rose colored glasses on when it comes to their partners because of their inherent need to fix everything.
I’m being a cool girl, I’m keeping it so tight

The term “cool girl” gained a slightly new meaning after the rise in popularity of a monologue in the movie Gone Girl, based off the book by the same name. In the monologue https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0o4heKCLeTs
the main character, Amy, talks about all the hoops she had to jump through to keep her husband interested in her and to conform to be what he wanted in a wife.

This song seemingly tells the tale of a relationship in which the narrator, is giving a lot more than they’re getting, allowing for the above connection. A scenario in which they do everything to align with what their partner wants, while their partner does nothing for them.

description.plain:
On August 4th, 2022, Katie Gregson-Macleod first posted about Complex when she published a minute long clip on TikTok with the caption: “here’s my saviour complex song.” A clever nod to the song “Savior Complex” off Phoebe Bridgers‘ sophomore album, Punisher, which complex was inspired by.

The clip quickly gained traction and within the first four days it racked up 2.5 million views and over 500K likes. The comment section was full of people relating to the lyrics of the song, as well as pop stars Maisie Peters, Gracie Abrams, Mae Muller and Fletcher among others posting their praise.

Following this, she released the demo on August 26th, 2022 before releasing this version on October 7th, 2022.

annotations: I need him like water, he lives on a landslide
Water is essential in life, akin to this context wherein she cannot live without her “water”, or him. Water triggers landslide, her intense need for him causes a downfall in the end.
But I’m wearing his boxers, I’m being a good wife

This may be a reference to the popular trend on TikTok –the app where “complex” was originally released– where women wear their boyfriend’s boxers to elicit a reaction, usually with the intent to turn their partner on.

The narrator is trying to be a good wife by being appealing to their partner.
